26 20-56-101. Prohibition on over-the-counter diet pills to a person
27 under eighteen years of age.
28 (a) As used in this section:
29 (1)(A) “Over-the-counter diet pills” means a class of drugs that
30 is labeled and marketed under the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act, 21
31 U.S.C. § 301 et seq., as existing on January 1, 2025, for the purpose of
32 achieving weight loss that is lawfully sold, transferred, or otherwise
33 furnished without a prescription.
34 (B) “Over-the-counter diet pills” includes a product
35 marketed with a drug facts panel under federal regulations that contains
36 either approved drug ingredients or ingredients deemed adulterated under 21
